---
description: Rules for all test files (pytest, Jest, Playwright)
globs: ["**/tests/**/*.py", "frontend/src/**/*.test.{ts,tsx}", "e2e/**/*.spec.ts"]
alwaysApply: false
---

## TDD order — never skip

1. Write failing unit test
2. Write failing integration test
3. Implement until green
4. Write component test (MSW mocks)
5. Implement component until green
6. Write E2E test
7. Write `@pytest.mark.llm` test if LLM is involved

## Integration test must-haves (every route)

Every integration test file must cover:
- ✅ Happy path (correct role + valid data)
- ✅ Missing auth → 401
- ✅ Wrong role → 403
- ✅ Cross-studio violation → 403
- ✅ Invalid input → 422
- ✅ Not found → 404

## LLM test assertions — never assert string length

```python
# CORRECT — key presence + type
assert isinstance(wo["title"], str) and wo["title"]

# WRONG — brittle, will flap
assert len(wo["title"]) < 100
```

## Pytest fixtures

- Use `db_session` (rolled-back transaction) — never commit in tests
- Use factories from `backend/tests/factories.py` — never insert raw SQL
- Mark slow LLM tests: `@pytest.mark.llm`

## Frontend tests

- Use MSW handlers — never mock `fetch` directly
- Use `@testing-library/user-event` — never `fireEvent`
- Every component test must include a viewer/unauthorised case

## Playwright

- Always use Page Object Model from `e2e/pages/`
- Never write raw `page.click()` in spec files
- LLM proxy is active in E2E — never hit real LLM API
